<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,303,1033,1059]" box="[189,303,1033,1059]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1033,1059]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1033,1059]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,1082,1262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
This species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moczar 1970 a)" baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[698,1048,1082,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Metrionotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,841,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Metrionotus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L." box="[863,1040,1082,1108]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="409 - 451" refId="ref7559" refString="Moczar L. 1970 a. Mesitiinae of world, genera Sulcomesitius Moczar and Metronotus Moczar. II. (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 16: 409 - 451." type="journal article" year="1970">Móczár 1970a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1286,1082,1108]" name="South Africa" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="409 - 451" refId="ref7559" refString="Moczar L. 1970 a. Mesitiinae of world, genera Sulcomesitius Moczar and Metronotus Moczar. II. (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 16: 409 - 451." type="journal article" year="1970">Móczár 1970a</bibRefCitation>
), and was later recorded from the 
<collectingCountry box="[654,906,1120,1146]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O." box="[920,1222,1120,1147]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="375 - 404" refId="ref7132" refString="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O. 2011 Order Hymenoptera, family Bethylidae, subfamily Mesitiinae. In: Harten A. van (ed.) Arthropod Fauna of UAE. Vol. 4: 375 - 404. Dar Al Ummah Printing, Publishing, Distribution &amp; Advertising, Abu Dhabi." type="journal article" year="2011">Barbosa &amp;Azevedo 2011</bibRefCitation>
). We examined one male from 
<collectingCountry box="[374,434,1159,1185]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">UAE</collectingCountry>
deposited at UFES, and the analyses reveal that their characteristics correspond to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[221,380,1198,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[221,380,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[390,499,1198,1224]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Thus, we propose a new combination for this species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1223,1366,1198,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Metrionotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1223,1366,1198,1223]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Metrionotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,348,1236,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,348,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[355,462,1236,1262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
